<article data-view="I4" contenteditable="true" tabindex="1"><h1>Signals</h1><p>A&nbsp;<span style="font-style: italic;">signal&nbsp;</span>signifies a communication within the framework.&nbsp; There are different types of signals that identifies the communication method "channel" that the signal propagation is traversing.</p><p>For example:</p><ul><li>Apply:</li><li>Call:</li><li>Message:</li><li>Event:</li><li>Broadcast:&nbsp;</li></ul><ol><li>asdfasdfad</li><li>sdfasdf</li><ol><li>asdfasdfasdfas</li><li>sadfasdf</li></ol><li>asdfasdfs</li></ol><p>The signal data is carried through a&nbsp;<i>message.&nbsp;</i>A message can be a string identifying the signal's&nbsp;<i>topic&nbsp;</i>or any mutable object with a&nbsp;<b>topic&nbsp;</b>property.&nbsp;</p><p>An&nbsp;<i>Owner&nbsp;</i>is a receiver that receives messages and propagates them within its ownership scope.&nbsp; Owners have a signal object whose methods perform the propagation.&nbsp; For example:</p><ul><li><u>owner.signal.Message</u></li></ul><p><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">is the method to propagate a Message signal.&nbsp; When a message is propagated, it is assigned a Symbol.Signal property identifying the signal/propagation.</span></p><p><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">As signals propagate, the message is sent to&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: sans-serif;"><i>receiver&nbsp;</i></span><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">nodes within the channel graph.&nbsp; A receiver is any&nbsp;object with a&nbsp;</span><b style="font-family: sans-serif;">receive</b><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">(message)</span><span style="font-family: sans-serif; font-weight: bold;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">method.&nbsp; The receiver determines whether it will interact with the message through the topic and other state within a message object.</span></p><p><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">A control is a receiver that delegates some or all signal processing to its&nbsp;</span><b style="font-family: sans-serif;">controller.process&nbsp;</b><span style="font-family: sans-serif;">method.</span></p></article>